# Cursor AI Rules — Advanced Playwright Framework

## Quality Gates
Run these after EVERY code change. Do not mark a task complete until all pass:
1. `npm run typecheck` — zero TypeScript errors
2. `npm run lint` — zero ESLint errors
3. `npm run format:check` — all files formatted (run `npm run format` to auto-fix)
4. `npx playwright test --grep @smoke` — smoke suite green

## Project Structure
- Page Objects → `src/pages/` (extend BasePage)
- Fixtures → `src/fixtures/test-base.ts`
- Spec files → `src/tests/`
- Test data → `src/testdata/` (JSON · CSV · XLSX · types.ts)
- Utilities → `src/utils/` (logger, reporter, file reader, data factory)
- Config → `src/config/` (env URLs)

## Strict Rules
- Locators MUST be arrow functions: `btn = () => this.page.locator('#id')`
- All tests MUST have tags: `@smoke`, `@regression`, `@e2e`, `@P0`, `@P1`, or `@P2`
- Use path aliases: `@pages/`, `@utils/`, `@fixtures/`, `@testdata/`, `@config/`
- Use `createLogger('ClassName')` from `@utils/logger` for all logging
- No `as any`, no `// @ts-ignore`, no inline `eslint-disable` without reason
- Import test from `@fixtures/test-base`, not directly from `@playwright/test`

## TypeScript
- Strict mode is ON — all types must be explicit
- `noUnusedLocals` and `noUnusedParameters` are enabled — remove unused code
- `noImplicitReturns` is enabled — all code paths must return a value

## Commit Convention
feat: · fix: · refactor: · chore: · docs: · ci: · test:
